This article is a transcript of a background briefing given by senior administration officials on the first day of the COP26 climate summit. The officials discuss the actions taken by the United States to address the climate crisis, including the release of the U.S. long-term strategy to achieve net-zero greenhouse gas emissions by 2050, the launch of the PREPARE plan to help developing countries adapt to climate change, and the announcement of the Global Methane Pledge to reduce methane emissions. They also mention the upcoming launch of a plan to conserve global forests and highlight the importance of innovation and sectoral targets in tackling the climate crisis. The officials address questions about the status of climate legislation in Congress and the participation of other countries, such as China and Brazil, in global climate efforts.